1) Regression. We want to predict the amount somone will spend, a continious variable. 

2) Classification. Since the color variable is a classification and can only be a finite number of options. 

3) Regression. While we can look at the variable as continious because not many familys have more than 5 children, i think regression would be more ideal. 

4) Classification. Signing up for a service is a simple yes or no. 

5) Regression. Number of times someone will get sick is a continious variable.  

6) Classification. The answer is a yes or a no question.

7) Classification. Finite number of mediceds to be give as decided by the number of symptoms. 
